    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>You consume fire and hold it until you spit out the flames.</em></p><p>You can ingest a nonmagical fire up to the size of a Small campfire within range. The fire is stored harmlessly in your mouth and dissipates without effect if it is not expelled before the spell ends.</p><p>Once ingested, you can spit out the stored fire as an action. If you try to hit a particular target with the flames, treat this as a ranged attack with a range of 5 feet. Small campfire-sized flames deal 2d6 fire damage, while Tiny torch-sized flames deal 1d6 fire damage. Once you have spit out the flames, the fire goes out immediately unless it hits flammable material that can keep it fed.</p>",
      "source": {
        "fallback": "Black Flag Reference Document"
      },
      "short": "Eat fire, use it later."
    },
